      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HE'S A PEARL (2) is worth forgiving for his last effort when eighth (30.08) at Richmond over 520m. The form out of his last race has been franked. Tough to beat if on-song. FINE SHINE (3) goes very well at the course with five wins and a placing from nine starts. Placed last time (29.77) at Wentworth Park in a Grade 5, finishing second and beaten 0.8 lengths. Among the main chances. FASTENED (8) was never in contention last time after being shuffled back early at Warragul, but prior to that won easily by 7 lengths at Warragul (22.28) beating Mad Hatter Rose in a Grade 5 H on January 6. The form from his last run stacks up well. Should play a prominent role. TIN ROOF RUSTY (1) racing over this course and distance brings the best out in him.",
